EKG reveals atrial fibrillation with heart rate of 82.  The patient has anteroseptal infarct and nonspecific T-wave abnormality.
Chest x-ray reveals calcified granuloma of the left lower lobe.  The patient has left pleural effusion and/or pleural thickening.  The patient has associated parenchymal opacity at the left base that could represent rounded atelectasis.  The patient has moderate enlargement of the cardiac silhouette.  The patient has calcified tortuous aorta.  There is degenerative changes of the thoracic spine as well as a sternotomy.
