PLAN
I have discussed laboratory results with the patient as well as the chest x-ray and the EKG.  The patient has been asymptomatic.  He is on beta-blocker, ACE-inhibitor.  The patient is off Coumadin due to his current anemia and the planned procedure to remove his colon cancer.  The patient is going to see his surgeon on Thursday.  There is no need for an invasive management at this time, as the patient needs surgery if indicated and it will not change the plan of care.  The patient has multiple cardiovascular risk factors.  He has moderate surgical risk of perioperative cardiovascular morbidity/mortality of 5% to 10%.  The patient needs to continue on his beta-blocker during the preoperative period for a target heart rate of 60 beats per minute.  Volume overload will be risky during the perioperative time due to his history of congestive heart failure and he might need intravenous Lasix.  I advised the patient to contact his primary-care provider to increase the dose of potassium, especially if it is low, he might need to cut down slightly on the diuretic, because his sodium is getting at higher-level.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening. Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

